    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't that kind of a circular argument though? saying it failed because it didn't create a perfect democracy... does that mean any intervention that doesn't result in a stable liberal state is automatically a \"failure\" regardless of what happens on the ground during the actual mission? it feels like you're judging it by one specific standard rather than actual strategic outcomes.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
